title: For Sale/Trade:  Colt Boa
postcontent: NIB 4" Colt Boa 357 Most of us know the story but for those who do not.  The Colt Boa is the least manufactured of all Colt Snake guns.  In 1985 Colt manufactured 1.200 Colt Boas for Lew Horton distributing Co.. 600 Boas with a six inch barrel and 600 Boas with a 4 inch barrel. 100 of each were sold in 2 gun sets with a remaining of 500 6 inch and 500 4 inch Boas to sell individually.When purchased new Lew Horton also offered a free factory letter if oredered shortly after purchase.  Few buyers took advantage of this and this Boa is the only one i have owned or seen come up for sale with a factory letter dated shortly after purchase in 1985.  So a nice little bonus for the purist in collecting.  Again this Boa comes in its original number matching box and includes hang tag and all original paper work.  The Colt is unfired with the only distraction being a whisper of a turn line.  Very "FAINT".  This is a splendid example of the 4" Colt Boa.I am offering this at 11K and i am open to to partial trade/cash or multiple trades for this revolver.  I am interesed in an even trade for a NIB Colt Python 2 1/2 in "ORIGINAL" BSS finish.  I am not intersted in any trades that would "NOT" involve high quality firearms, including mini bikes, mopeds, segways, already have one, hunting dogs, bird feeders, horses, george forman grills, automobiles, mis behaved children etc. etc:).Things of interst Colt Python, Colt Troopers, Colt Vipers, Colt Detecive Specials, Colt Diamondback, Colt Cobras, Colt Anacond's, Colt King Cobr's.  Colt 1903, Colt 1908, Pre War Colt 38 Super and Prewar Colt 1911.  No military.Also Smith and Wesson 27 or Smith and wesson pre 27 and Smith and Wesson Pre 29.  Early Marlin 39 high condition or Marlin 1897 or Marlin 97 in high condition. I can email additional photos if you like and i am available on my cell.  six one 2 - three 2 seven- 1 6 six five.  My voicemail is not set up/ working on my cell.  If i noticed a missed call i will follow up.. title: For Sale:  COLT DS-II LNIB
postcontent: Here is a steal for someone that wants to own a rare Colt DS-II that was manufactured by Colt for only two years (1997 and 1998). Colt first named it Detective Special Two but Colt never used that designation, so the correct model name is the DS-II. The DS-II is built on the same "SF-VI" frame as the SF-VI model, and is in fact nothing more than the SF-VI with a new barrel stamp and a slightly thicker top strap to increase strength. This one comes in satin stainless with black Pachmayr grips with the molded Colt banner and logo. It is in mint condition and from the turnline, was either fired very lightly or action used without firing. Only distraction is one idiot mark on the right side of the back strap that can been seen from the photos which looks worse in the photo than it really does as it is zoomed in to show the mark. If it wasn’t for this small mark, this Colt DS-II would be much higher in price so this is why this Colt is steal at this price. This beautiful and rare Colt comes in the original box with documents. Please let us know if you would like to see any other pics of any part of this Colt. If you have been looking at a DS-II or just seeing this one for the first time, this is your Colt. As of 2007, Ruger has discontinued production. It is a semi-automatic carbine using a blowback action. The Carbine uses the same ammunition and magazines as the Ruger P Series 9mm and .40 S&W caliber pistols.Both the PC9 (the 9mm version) and the PC4 (.40 S&W) are patterned after the highly successful Ruger 10/22 carbine. The Carbine is intended as a shoulder weapon for police use, although it is available for sale to civilians as well. The intent is that an officer will carry a Ruger P Series pistol as a sidearm, and keep a Carbine available (for example, in his/her patrol vehicle) as a shoulder weapon if needed. Since the carbine has a 16-inch (410 mm) barrel, it provides more power with the same ammunition used by the 4-inch (100 mm) barreled pistol. The carbine also provides additional accuracy and range over the pistol.
